description.narrative: The Ministry of Education and Sports (MoES) developed the Sector Preparedness Plan to enhance quality and inclusiveness of education during the COVID 19 pandemic. However, the period that schools have been closed has resulted in loss of learning time, which has been replaced with a period of anxiety as children are now expected to learn from home through the provision of continuity of education programmes, including learning through TV, Radio and home learning kits. UNICEF has supported the development of this plan and provided support to alternative learning programmes, using different approaches to enhance learning during this period. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/07/2020
